<subSubSection pageId="160" pageNumber="161" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="160" pageNumber="161">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="160" pageNumber="161">
<bibRefCitation author="Pallary, P" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe d'Histoire Naturelle de l'Afrique du Nord" pageId="323" pageNumber="324" pagination="70 - 87" publicationUrl="http://bibdigital.rjb.csic.es/spa/Libro.php?Libro=1840" refId="B378" refString="Pallary, P, 1916. Observations relatives a la nomenclature des Melanopsis fossiles. Bulletin de la Societe d'Histoire Naturelle de l'Afrique du Nord 7 (3): 70 - 87, http://bibdigital.rjb.csic.es/spa/Libro.php?Libro=1840" title="Observations relatives a la nomenclature des Melanopsis fossiles." url="http://bibdigital.rjb.csic.es/spa/Libro.php?Libro=1840" volume="7" year="1916">Pallary (1916)</bibRefCitation>
erroneously treated &quot; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pallary" authorityYear="1916" class="Gastropoda" family="Melanopsidae" genus="Melanopsis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="magna" order="Pteropoda" pageId="160" pageNumber="161" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="magna">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="160" pageNumber="161">magna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; as available name attributed to 
<bibRefCitation author="Ferussac, AEJPJFd'Audebard de" journalOrPublisher="Memoires de la Societe d'Histoire Naturelle de Paris" pageId="308" pageNumber="309" pagination="132 - 164" publicationUrl="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/23445page/148/mode/1up" refId="B144" refString="Ferussac, AEJPJFd'Audebard de, 1823. Monographie des especes vivantes et fossiles du genre melanopside, Melanopsis, et observations geologiques a leur sujet. Memoires de la Societe d'Histoire Naturelle de Paris 1 (1): 132 - 164, http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/23445page/148/mode/1up" title="Monographie des especes vivantes et fossiles du genre melanopside, Melanopsis, et observations geologiques a leur sujet." url="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/23445page/148/mode/1up" volume="1" year="1823">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Férussac">Ferussac</normalizedToken>
(1823)
</bibRefCitation>
, who solely used the word as descriptive term (Latin 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“big”">&quot;big&quot;</normalizedToken>
), which he applied to many of his varieties. The name became nevertheless available from 
<bibRefCitation author="Pallary, P" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe d'Histoire Naturelle de l'Afrique du Nord" pageId="323" pageNumber="324" pagination="70 - 87" publicationUrl="http://bibdigital.rjb.csic.es/spa/Libro.php?Libro=1840" refId="B378" refString="Pallary, P, 1916. Observations relatives a la nomenclature des Melanopsis fossiles. Bulletin de la Societe d'Histoire Naturelle de l'Afrique du Nord 7 (3): 70 - 87, http://bibdigital.rjb.csic.es/spa/Libro.php?Libro=1840" title="Observations relatives a la nomenclature des Melanopsis fossiles." url="http://bibdigital.rjb.csic.es/spa/Libro.php?Libro=1840" volume="7" year="1916">Pallary (1916)</bibRefCitation>
who associated the name with an illustration in 
<bibRefCitation author="Ferussac, AEJPJFd'Audebard de" journalOrPublisher="Memoires de la Societe d'Histoire Naturelle de Paris" pageId="308" pageNumber="309" pagination="132 - 164" publicationUrl="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/23445page/148/mode/1up" refId="B144" refString="Ferussac, AEJPJFd'Audebard de, 1823. Monographie des especes vivantes et fossiles du genre melanopside, Melanopsis, et observations geologiques a leur sujet. Memoires de la Societe d'Histoire Naturelle de Paris 1 (1): 132 - 164, http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/23445page/148/mode/1up" title="Monographie des especes vivantes et fossiles du genre melanopside, Melanopsis, et observations geologiques a leur sujet." url="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/23445page/148/mode/1up" volume="1" year="1823">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Férussac">Ferussac</normalizedToken>
(1823
</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 7, fig. 16). The illustrated specimen is, however, the holotype (by monotypy) of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferussac" authorityYear="1822" class="Gastropoda" family="Melanopsidae" genus="Melanopsis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanopsis dufourii" order="Pteropoda" pageId="160" pageNumber="161" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="dufourii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="160" pageNumber="161">Melanopsis dufourii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Férussac">Ferussac</normalizedToken>
, 1822 (
<normalizedToken originalValue="Férussac">Ferussac</normalizedToken>
used the same plates in both of his works and thus Pallary actually referred to the specimen illustrated as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferussac" authorityYear="1822" class="Gastropoda" family="Melanopsidae" genus="Melanopsis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanopsis dufourii" order="Pteropoda" pageId="160" pageNumber="161" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="dufourii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="160" pageNumber="161">Melanopsis dufourii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the &quot;Histoire naturelle&quot;; see also introduction and Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Ferussac's original figure legends of the two plates of &quot; Melanopsides fossiles &quot; (1822 / 1823) in the &quot; Histoire naturelle &quot;, compared with the altered legends supplied by Deshayes in 1839 when finalizing the work. Note that Ferussac's original figure legends for plate 1 are unavailable to me and thus based on the legends for plate 7 in Ferussac (1823), which are supposed to be identical (see text for details)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/3E6FCC01983F825DC2CEDBCDC3712B51" pageId="160" pageNumber="161" tableUuid="3E6FCC01983F825DC2CEDBCDC3712B51">1</tableCitation>
for details of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Férussac’s">Ferussac's</normalizedToken>
publications). Therefore, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pallary" authorityYear="1916" class="Gastropoda" family="Melanopsidae" genus="Melanopsis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanopsis magna" order="Pteropoda" pageId="160" pageNumber="161" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="magna">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="160" pageNumber="161">Melanopsis magna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Pallary, 1916 is a junior objective synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferussac" authorityYear="1822" class="Gastropoda" family="Melanopsidae" genus="Melanopsis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanopsis dufourii" order="Pteropoda" pageId="160" pageNumber="161" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="dufourii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="160" pageNumber="161">Melanopsis dufourii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
